message: The 'growth serum' tool is key to increasing value. Start by using it on a small, flying creature like the bird or bee; this usually yields 5 points. Next, combine this 'grown' flying creature with a land animal to create a hybrid, which should be worth 10 points. Then, apply the 'growth serum' to this combined hybrid. You can usually do this twice more, increasing the value significantly each time (e.g., to 25-30, then to 35-40). Be careful not to apply 'growth serum' to the same item more than three times total (initial application + two more on the combined item), as further applications will drastically drop the item's value. The 'mutation catalyst' tool consistently reduced item values in my experience, so it's best to avoid it. Aim for a score around 35-40 and then submit to maximize your score and avoid over-crafting.

message: Focus on creating small combined items with the growth serum. Combining two small items with different habitats (e.g., land and air) initially gives value 5, but even two small items of the same habitat (value 0) can be grown. Repeatedly apply the growth serum to these small items: 'grown' increases value, 'super-grown' increases more, and 'ultra-grown' gives the highest values (up to 35). Avoid using the mutation catalyst as it consistently reduces value. Also, be careful with 'super-growing' or 'ultra-growing' items made from medium or large components, as their value drops sharply after the first growth application and can go negative.

Over-growing with the serum beyond 'grown' (e.g., 'super-grown', 'ultra-grown') generally leads to negative values. Don't be afraid of the first 'mutant' step going negative, as it's a necessary bridge to 'super-mutant'.
